a-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ikXwFM hZHGfK pf-45_">Alpaca wool wicks sweat away from your body to help keep you warm and dry.</span></li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:4;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-TtZnY gnBPmJ pf-46_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0071/4748/7305/t/11/assets/pf-2181cea2--Sustainable-clothing-alpaca_300x.jpg?v=1595219735" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0071/4748/7305/t/11/assets/pf-2181cea2--Sustainable-clothing-alpaca.jpg?v=1595219735 1536w" width="300" height="300" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="Woman in black alpaca wool sweater womens hugging an alpaca" title="Soft, cozy alpaca wool sweater" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-khIgEk hQhHpX pf-47_"/></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-eKYRIR llyViG pf-48_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hmbstg iriXCP"><div class="sc-hiKfDv dRsyqq pf-49_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-TtZnY gnBPmJ pf-50_"><div class="sc-hiKfDv dRsyqq pf-51_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:8;--c-lg:8"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-TtZnY gnBPmJ pf-52_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-dPaNzc kXWuay pf-53_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ikXwFM hZHGfK pf-55_">2)  FUNCTIONAL FIT FOR OUTDOOR SPORT &amp; TRAVEL</span></h2><p class="sc-daBunf bWmajK pf-56_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ikXwFM hZHGfK pf-58_">Our <a href="https://armsofandes.com/collections/mens-wool-winter-jackets" target="_blank" style="font-weight: bold; color: rgb(237, 115, 50);">men's alpaca wool sweater</a>&nbsp;and women’s equivalents are designed with travel and outdoor sports in mind, so you can stay warm whatever you’re doing.</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-kHWWYL zRuTu pf-59_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hOPeYd eXirsP pf-60_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ikXwFM hZHGfK pf-62_">Designed to fit snugly to your body shape, our base and mid layers move with you as you climb, ski or hike.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hOPeYd eXirsP pf-63_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ikXwFM hZHGfK pf-65_">The longer length and elongated back panel ensure extended coverage, so you won’t feel exposed when reaching up or bending over.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hOPeYd eXirsP pf-66_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ikXwFM hZHGfK pf-68_">The sleeves are extra-long and thumb holes help keep them in place to form a cozy seal, as well as making layering easier.</span></li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:4;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-TtZnY gnBPmJ pf-69_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0071/4748/7305/t/11/assets/pf-7b1a8f25--Arms-of-andes-mens-alpaca-hoodie-sweater_300x.jpg?v=1597090043" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0071/4748/7305/t/11/assets/pf-7b1a8f25--Arms-of-andes-mens-alpaca-hoodie-sweater.jpg?v=1597090043 1536w" width="300" height="300" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="Two men wearing alpaca wool sweater base layers in the mountains" title="Alpaca wool sweater - Designed to move with you " data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-khIgEk hQhHpX pf-70_"/></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-eKYRIR llyViG pf-71_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hmbstg iriXCP"><div class="sc-hiKfDv dRsyqq pf-72_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-TtZnY gnBPmJ pf-73_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-dPaNzc kXWuay pf-74_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ikXwFM hZHGfK pf-76_">3)&nbsp; SUSTAINABLE WOOL FROM THE MOST ECO-FRIENDLY ANIMAL</span></h2><div class="sc-hiKfDv dRsyqq pf-77_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-TtZnY gnBPmJ pf-78_"><p class="sc-daBunf bWmajK pf-79_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ikXwFM hZHGfK pf-81_">Peruvian alpacas are raised in the Andes mountains, their natural habitat, so they have developed adaptations which allow them to live in synergy with the environment.&nbsp;<br></span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-kHWWYL zRuTu pf-82_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hOPeYd eXirsP pf-83_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ikXwFM hZHGfK pf-85_">&nbsp;When grazing, alpacas cut the grass with their teeth instead of yanking it from the root, promoting regrowth.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hOPeYd eXirsP pf-86_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ikXwFM hZHGfK pf-88_">Alpacas have soft, padded feet, so they don’t damage the ground or contribute to erosion.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hOPeYd eXirsP pf-89_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ikXwFM hZHGfK pf-91_">&nbsp;To prevent contamination of food and water sources, alpaca flocks defecate in common dung piles and their poop is used by farmers as fertilizer and biomass fuel!</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-fXazdy UjHkE pf-92_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0071/4748/7305/t/11/assets/pf-35f368d0--alpaca-in-their-natural-environment-in-peru_500x.jpg?v=1594899206" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0071/4748/7305/t/11/assets/pf-35f368d0--alpaca-in-their-natural-environment-in-peru.jpg?v=1594899206 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0071/4748/7305/t/11/assets/pf-35f368d0--alpaca-in-their-natural-environment-in-peru_1000x.jpg?v=1594899206 